@tqchen  I am able to predictions for batch of images but it takes 4 seconds to get predictions for 8 images ie. i did not get any speed gain through batching.
Is there any way to get prediction results faster for batch of images in cpu mode?
Right now i am using the c prediction api , will using the cpp interface lead to better performance?

 Maybe you can learn from the code example-"simple_bind" `https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/example/notebooks/simple_bind.ipynb`

the code to initialize the parameters of aux_states  is like this

```
aux_dict = dict(zip(aux_names, [mx.nd.zeros(shape, ctx=ctx) for shape in aux_shapes]))
for key, arr in aux_dict.items():
    if "gamma" in key:
        aux_dict[key][:] = 1
    elif "bias" in key:
        aux_dict[key][:] = 0
    elif "beta" in key:
        aux_dict[key][:] = 0
```

@tqchen Thanks for your advice.
- I trained it with batch size of 16 on single GPU Titan Black.
- I'll test only LSTM side later.
